What decisions do you face?
I fly regualty because of 

## Seven templates

Training Kit (https://learn.lambdaschool.com/ds/module/recedjanlbpqxic2r) explains the seven templates from Priceonomics.

Can you apply the templates to your topics? 

1. Geographic Variation
Areas that planes go down

2. Trend related to the news
How much media coverage crashes get

3. Who does that?
Which airline/countries have the most accidents?

4. Answering a question people care about
How many planes crash vs total flights>

5. Valuable to businesses
Advertising certain brands which are extremely safe, like cars

6. What's the most popular?
This would be bad optics, horserace for airlines with most crashes over the past 100 years

7. Cost/Money rankings
Crash cost 

## Misconceptions

What misconceptions do people have about your topic?
Align with my own misconceptions? Crashes are common enough to worry about

## Examples

What data storytelling example inspires you?
The majority of these are from the 1st half of the century, many downes planes during wwii 

Could you do a new hypothesis, for the same question?
Crashes have gone down over the years or have not

Could you do a new question, for the same topic?
Longer flights have more crashes?

Could you do a new topic, with the same "style"?
Car accidents 

